critical bottleneck: Iran has officially ruled out \"direct talks\" in Islamabad. For anyone analyzing the resolution requirements of this market, this is a decisive logistical red flag.\n\nA \"Permanent Peace Deal\" of this magnitude involves complex legal drafting and verification that cannot be achieved through proxy messaging and intermediaries in under 120 hours. The transition from \"refusing to meet\" to a \"Definitively Established Permanent Agreement\" by April 30th is a bureaucratic and legal impossibility. \n\nThis mission by the US delegation is clearly a \"probing session\" to hear positions, not a signing ceremony for a historic treaty. The diplomatic friction is simply too high for an April resolution. Logic dictates that a deal is not permanent if the parties aren't even in the same room.\n\nSource: https://www.reuters.com/world/middle-east/us-negotiators-go-islamabad-iran-says-no-direct-talks-2026-04-25/","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":357807,"userAddress":"0x5dfeecd3af4258c1a0fd0890c1b6ffefc0292673","createdAt":"2026-04-25T10:34:56.194492Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-25T10:35:07.037812Z","profile":{"name":"morenaji","pseudonym":"Ignorant-Case","displayUsernamePublic":true,"bio":"Trading the delta between diplomatic optics and legal reality. Permanent means Permanent. 🏛️","proxyWallet":"0x8a37bbf79eba56e84beb04a270d62da2424ea71d","baseAddress":"0x5dfeecd3af4258c1a0fd0890c1b6ffefc0292673","profileImage":"https://polymarket-upload.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/profile-image-5439026-0dd2f301-c2c7-4f1d-8d46-ac1295c5d2c1.webp"},"reactions":[{"id":"2803383","commentID":2839819,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x217eeec3ad18c9483dd6a7eb7729ff4733ba7559","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x164842ccb45ef1e06ffd74a1c6dba93e84cca676"}},{"id":"2803627","commentID":2839819,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x214cf9fba225e46bbd5bd1fd976e51011548536b","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x3b6521f671d033add846b1ab02cab6e596557584"}},{"id":"2803652","commentID":2839819,"